## Rationale

When using SequenceReader, it would nice to be able to limit calls to TryReadTo by passing an int for a maxReadSize. This would make all calls to TryReadTo* return preemptively if they read too much. These apis would be useful for parsing scenarios where we have a limit on the max length allowed for a value.

Without this API, I don't see a great way to limit a read size without slicing the ReadOnlySequence to a certain length before creating the SequenceReader

```c#
namespace System.Buffers
{
    public ref struct SequenceReader<T> where T : unmanaged, IEquatable<T>
    {
        public bool TryAdvanceTo(T delimiter, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryAdvanceToAny(ReadOnlySpan<T> delimiters, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);

        public bool TryReadTo(out ReadOnlySpan<T> span, T delimiter, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryReadTo(out ReadOnlySpan<T> span, T delimiter, T delimiterEscape, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryReadTo(out ReadOnlySpan<T> span, ReadOnlySpan<T> delimiter, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryReadToAny(out ReadOnlySpan<T> span, ReadOnlySpan<T> delimiters, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);

        public bool TryReadTo(out ReadOnlySequence<T> sequence, T delimiter, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryReadTo(out ReadOnlySequence<T> sequence, T delimiter, T delimiterEscape, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryReadTo(out ReadOnlySequence<T> sequence, ReadOnlySpan<T> delimiter, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
        public bool TryReadToAny(out ReadOnlySequence<T> sequence, ReadOnlySpan<T> delimiters, bool advancePastDelimiter = true, int maxReadSize = -1);
    }
}
```

The hard part of this type of API is knowing whether the TryReadTo call returned false due to not finding the delimiter or because it reached the maxReadSize. This can either be done through comparing Consumed before and after calling TryReadTo*.

